824  struct DefaultEventFormatter : public EventFormatter {

826  virtual std::string format(const UnexpectedMethodCallEvent &e) override {
827  std::ostringstream out;
828  out << "Unexpected method invocation: ";
829  out << e.getInvocation().format() << std::endl;
830  if (UnexpectedType::Unmatched == e.getUnexpectedType()) {
831  out << " Could not find Any recorded behavior to support this method call.";

845  out << formatExpectedPattern(expectedPattern) << std::endl;

849  out << std::endl;
850 
851  out << "Actual matches : " << e.actualCount() << std::endl;
852 
853  auto actualSequence = e.actualSequence();
854  out << "Actual sequence : total of " << actualSequence.size() << " actual invocations";
855  if (actualSequence.size() == 0) {
856  out << ".";
857  } else {
858  out << ":" << std::endl;
859  }
860  formatInvocationList(out, actualSequence);
861 
862  return out.str();
863  }
864 
865  virtual std::string format(const NoMoreInvocationsVerificationEvent &e) override {
866  std::ostringstream out;
867  out << "Verification error" << std::endl;
868  out << "Expected no more invocations!! But the following unverified invocations were found:" << std::endl;
869  formatInvocationList(out, e.unverifedIvocations());
870  return out.str();
871  }
872 
873  private:
874 
875  static std::string formatSequence(const Sequence &val) {
876  const ConcatenatedSequence *cs = dynamic_cast<const ConcatenatedSequence *>(&val);
877  if (cs) {
878  return format(*cs);
879  }
880  const RepeatedSequence *rs = dynamic_cast<const RepeatedSequence *>(&val);
881  if (rs) {
882  return format(*rs);
883  }
884 
885 
886  std::vector<Invocation::Matcher *> vec;
887  val.getExpectedSequence(vec);
888  return vec[0]->format();
889  }
890 
891  static void formatExpectedCount(std::ostream &out, fakeit::VerificationType verificationType,
892  int expectedCount) {
893  if (verificationType == fakeit::VerificationType::Exact)
894  out << "exactly ";
895 
896  if (verificationType == fakeit::VerificationType::AtLeast)
897  out << "at least ";
898 
899  out << expectedCount;
900  }
901 
902  static void formatInvocationList(std::ostream &out, const std::vector<fakeit::Invocation *> &actualSequence) {
903  size_t max_size = actualSequence.size();
904  if (max_size > 5)
905  max_size = 5;
906 
907  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < max_size; i++) {
908  out << " ";
909  auto invocation = actualSequence[i];
910  out << invocation->format();
911  if (i < max_size - 1)
912  out << std::endl;
913  }
914 
915  if (actualSequence.size() > max_size)
916  out << std::endl << " ...";
917  }
918 
919  static std::string format(const ConcatenatedSequence &val) {
920  std::ostringstream out;
921  out << formatSequence(val.getLeft()) << " + " << formatSequence(val.getRight());
922  return out.str();
923  }
924 
925  static std::string format(const RepeatedSequence &val) {
926  std::ostringstream out;
927  const ConcatenatedSequence *cs = dynamic_cast<const ConcatenatedSequence *>(&val.getSequence());
928  const RepeatedSequence *rs = dynamic_cast<const RepeatedSequence *>(&val.getSequence());
929  if (rs || cs)
930  out << '(';
931  out << formatSequence(val.getSequence());
932  if (rs || cs)
933  out << ')';
934 
935  out << " * " << val.getTimes();
936  return out.str();
937  }
938 
939  static std::string formatExpectedPattern(const std::vector<fakeit::Sequence *> &expectedPattern) {
940  std::string expectedPatternStr;
941  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < expectedPattern.size(); i++) {
942  Sequence *s = expectedPattern[i];
943  expectedPatternStr += formatSequence(*s);
944  if (i < expectedPattern.size() - 1)
945  expectedPatternStr += " ... ";
946  }
947  return expectedPatternStr;
948  }
949  };

8502  struct MatchAnalysis {
8503  std::vector<Invocation *> actualSequence;
8504  std::vector<Invocation *> matchedInvocations;
8505  int count;
8506 
8507  void run(InvocationsSourceProxy &involvedInvocationSources, std::vector<Sequence *> &expectedPattern) {
8508  getActualInvocationSequence(involvedInvocationSources, actualSequence);
8509  count = countMatches(expectedPattern, actualSequence, matchedInvocations);
8510  }
8511 
8512  private:
8513  static void getActualInvocationSequence(InvocationsSourceProxy &involvedMocks,
8514  std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence) {
8515  std::unordered_set<Invocation *> actualInvocations;
8516  collectActualInvocations(involvedMocks, actualInvocations);
8517  InvocationUtils::sortByInvocationOrder(actualInvocations, actualSequence);
8518  }
8519 
8520  static int countMatches(std::vector<Sequence *> &pattern, std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8521  std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations) {
8522  int end = -1;
8523  int count = 0;
8524  int startSearchIndex = 0;
8525  while (findNextMatch(pattern, actualSequence, startSearchIndex, end, matchedInvocations)) {
8526  count++;
8527  startSearchIndex = end;
8528  }
8529  return count;
8530  }
8531 
8532  static void collectActualInvocations(InvocationsSourceProxy &involvedMocks,
8533  std::unordered_set<Invocation *> &actualInvocations) {
8534  involvedMocks.getActualInvocations(actualInvocations);
8535  }
8536 
8537  static bool findNextMatch(std::vector<Sequence *> &pattern, std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8538  int startSearchIndex, int &end,
8539  std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations) {
8540  for (auto sequence : pattern) {
8541  int index = findNextMatch(sequence, actualSequence, startSearchIndex);
8542  if (index == -1) {
8543  return false;
8544  }
8545  collectMatchedInvocations(actualSequence, matchedInvocations, index, sequence->size());
8546  startSearchIndex = index + sequence->size();
8547  }
8548  end = startSearchIndex;
8549  return true;
8550  }
8551 
8552 
8553  static void collectMatchedInvocations(std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8554  std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations, int start,
8555  int length) {
8556  int indexAfterMatchedPattern = start + length;
8557  for (; start < indexAfterMatchedPattern; start++) {
8558  matchedInvocations.push_back(actualSequence[start]);
8559  }
8560  }
8561 
8562 
8563  static bool isMatch(std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8564  std::vector<Invocation::Matcher *> &expectedSequence, int start) {
8565  bool found = true;
8566  for (unsigned int j = 0; found && j < expectedSequence.size(); j++) {
8567  Invocation *actual = actualSequence[start + j];
8568  Invocation::Matcher *expected = expectedSequence[j];
8569  found = found && expected->matches(*actual);
8570  }
8571  return found;
8572  }
8573 
8574  static int findNextMatch(Sequence *&pattern, std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence, int startSearchIndex) {
8575  std::vector<Invocation::Matcher *> expectedSequence;
8576  pattern->getExpectedSequence(expectedSequence);
8577  for (int i = startSearchIndex; i < ((int) actualSequence.size() - (int) expectedSequence.size() + 1); i++) {
8578  if (isMatch(actualSequence, expectedSequence, i)) {
8579  return i;
8580  }
8581  }
8582  return -1;
8583  }
8584 
8585  };
8586 }

8640  void VerifyExpectation(VerificationEventHandler &verificationErrorHandler) {
8641  if (_isVerified)
8642  return;
8643  _isVerified = true;
8644 
8645  MatchAnalysis ma;
8646  ma.run(_involvedInvocationSources, _expectedPattern);
8647 
8648  if (isAtLeastVerification() && atLeastLimitNotReached(ma.count)) {
8649  return handleAtLeastVerificationEvent(verificationErrorHandler, ma.actualSequence, ma.count);
8650  }
8651 
8652  if (isExactVerification() && exactLimitNotMatched(ma.count)) {
